## 2. The ESP-IDF Project Structure

Every ESP-IDF project has the same folder structure. This is not optional — CMake and idf.py expect exactly this layout.

```
my_project/
|
+-- CMakeLists.txt          <- Top-level build file (Project level)
+-- sdkconfig                <- Generated config (never edit this)
+-- sdkconfig.defaults        <- Your config overrides (edit this)
+-- dependencies.lock       <- Component versions (auto-generated)
|
+-- main/                   <- Your main application component
|   +-- CMakeLists.txt      <- Main component build file
|   +-- main.c              <- Entry point — app_main() lives here
|   +-- main.h              <- Optional header
|
+-- components/             <- Your custom reusable components
|   +-- my_sensor/
|       +-- CMakeLists.txt
|       +-- my_sensor.h
|       +-- my_sensor.c
|
+-- build/                   <- Generated output (never commit this)
    +-- my_project.bin      <- Final firmware binary
    +-- bootloader/
    +-- partition_table/
```

