## 6. Menuconfig — Configuring Your Project

Menuconfig is a graphical configuration system built into ESP-IDF. It lets you configure hundreds of project settings without editing any code.

```bash
idf.py menuconfig
```

This opens an interactive menu in your terminal:

```
ESP-IDF Configuration
|
+-- Component config
|   |
|   +-- FreeRTOS
|   |   +-- Kernel tick frequency (Hz)         [1000]
|   |   +-- Maximum task priorities              [25]
|   |   +-- Enable task watchdog              [yes]
|   |
|   +-- WiFi
|   |   +-- WiFi static RX buffer number        [10]
|   |   +-- WiFi NVS flash                     [yes]
|   |   +-- WiFi task core ID                 [0]
|   |
|   +-- Log output
|       +-- Default log verbosity               [Info]
|
+-- Application configuration  <- YOUR custom settings go here
    +-- WiFi SSID               [your_network]
    +-- WiFi Password           [your_password]
    +-- MQTT Broker URL         [mqtt://broker:1883]
```

### PC Analogy

Menuconfig is like the **Windows Control Panel** or **BIOS settings** for your firmware.

|Menuconfig setting|PC equivalent|
|---|---|
|FreeRTOS tick rate|Windows scheduler frequency|
|Log verbosity|Windows Event Log level|
|WiFi buffer size|Network adapter buffer size|
|Flash encryption|BitLocker encryption|
|Bootloader log level|BIOS verbose mode|
|Task watchdog timeout|Windows hang detection timeout|

### Navigation Keys in Menuconfig

|Key|Action|
|---|---|
|Arrow keys|Move up/down|
|Enter|Open submenu / select|
|Space|Toggle yes/no options|
|Esc|Go back one level|
|/|Search for a setting|
|?|Show help for current item|
|S|Save configuration|
|Q|Quit|

